spanGrp.span: Me, I'm called Unyangi, I'm of Gwerigweeg
Mimi naitwa Unyangi ni wa Gwerigweg
I marred Hamisi, the grandson of Gombanera
Nimeolewa na Hamisi mjukuu wa Gombanera
iru bahati mbay gwargwedeeny qabar beshaki
Later unfortunately my husband was killed by an elephant
Baadaye kwa bahati mbaya mume wangu ameuawa na Tembo
qaqusch gew aa debugees gandaw debuug damanag
I am alone with my children
Niko peke yangu na watoto wangu
Us, when we were growing up
aa iimuch geng'adiisch geng'aday marebajeega geng'aday mahembeeg aa agwajeeg
Later we were growing marabajeega, mahembeega, and corn
Siku nyingine huwa tunalima marebajega,mahembega na mahindi
We would grind it with a grinding stone
The butakajeega, often we would pound
Butakajega huwa tunatuwanga kwa kutumia kiyuri
And another day you are pounding
qat diit ba qayiin aa qat sind qamn
That time in the old days, and now
Kipindi kile cha zamani na wa sasa
aa much iihees aqwayng'w ging'ash ng'anang'an
And later if you grow your food you grind everything
Na siku nyingine ukiivisha chakula chako unasaga kila siku
giram mbogaag ab gahar aa giwun ng'asheen
You fetch your corn inside and go to grind
Unachota mahindi yako ndani na kwenda kusaga
kuring'an aa gadiyoojig ab jeed quwari
Depending on what work remains at home
Kulingana kazi zilivyozidi ndani ya nyumba
And if you postpone you go to farm with your husband
Na ukiahirisha mnaenda kulima na mume wako
You put the firewood on your head and carry the child
Unaweka kuni kichwani na unambeba mtoto
aa nuny quwar gwalanyand qwasool gisirjand
Until home, and your man will take the hoe
Mpaka nyumbani na mzee anachukua jembe
Even your hoe you put inside the firewood, he won't help you
Hata jembe lako utweka ndani ya kuni maana hatakusaidia
aa iyoyid quwar niny gogoftad abosh ba gumd getan
And if you arrive home he will go to sit under the tree
Na mkifika nyumbani yeye anaenda kuketi chini ya mti
ging'ed un jeed end ginuny bid senga
You go to fetch, then you go to get firewood
Unaenda kuchota kisha unaenda kuchuma kuni
You cook and give him food
You eat the food, when it is done
You return to wash your dishes
iri niny iiqohiidooj quwar aa migad gagadiy goftaad ab gumd geet
If he returns home he doesn't do any more work, he sits underneath the tree
Yeye mkishafika nyumbani hafanyi kazi tena anakaa chini ya mti
rakin qamn dab much gelab jerkwed iindaw qwengag gwalanyand giqany qwasol gisirjan
But these days if you come from the field, if you have firewood, he takes the hoe
Lakini siku hizi mkitoka shambani ukiwa na kuni anachukua jembe
aa iyohiid quwar qany qwasol ee
And if you arrive home he takes
gwand ga solaj aa ga manung'qwasol ga heew giyeet
There are those who like to take it and those who don't want help
Kuna wanaochukua na ambao hawataki msaada
giqwasool basker aa go gwayad beeg
He will take the bicycle to look for water
Now you, as a woman, you are cooking
Kwa hapo wewe kama mama unapika
If he is done you return to the field
